#)Import Statements
â€¢ What It Is: Allows you to use classes from other packages.
â€¢ Why It's Used: Saves time by reusing code from the Java library or other
sources.
â€¢ Example: import java.util.Scanner;
â€¢ Note: Think of it as bringing in tools from a toolbox to use in your program.



1. Interpreter: Translates code line-by-line.
2. Compiler: Translates entire code at once.
3. Assembler: Converts assembly language to machine code.

